            . I am the wife of Michael Skallan; we live in <placeName id="t18320906-424-crimeloc2392">Hemlock-court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-424-crimeloc2392" type="placeName" value="Hemlock-court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-424-crimeloc2392" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-424-off2390 t18320906-424-crimeloc2392"></join>. On the 19th of August my daughter Catherine, who is six years old, went out to play; she had a coral necklace on - she called me about five o'clock, and said a woman wanted me; I went out, and missed the necklace - I saw the prisoner at Bow-street, in custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-424-person3434">
                  MARY 
                  ANN
               <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3434" type="surname" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3434" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3434" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             IRONSIDE. I live in Hemlock-court. On Sunday, the 19th of August, I saw the little girl, about four o'clock, with the necklace - I missed her all at once, but about five o'clock I was going down the court, and saw the prisoner bring her to No.19, and go in there; I sat down at my door, and the prisoner brought the <rs id="t18320906-424-viclabel2393" type="occupation">child</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-424-victim3432 t18320906-424-viclabel2393"></join> out of No.19 again, and I took her to her own mother's door, and said to her, "Go and tell your mother I want to speak to her," and then she went away; the child had no necklace on then.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-424-person3435">
                  JOHN 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3435" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3435" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-424-person3435" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a lodging-house. I have seen the prisoner frequently; on that Sunday night she brought me the coral necklace, and asked me if I would let her have 1s. on it, as she had had nothing to eat all day, and there was no pawnbroker's open - I let her have 1s., out of compassion, and the next morning she came and said her old man, who is a coachman, would not go out without his breakfast, and would I lend her another shilling, which I did, and the officer came and took the necklace.</p>

